-WHAT THE BACK OF THE CASE SAYS-
	&quot;Action explodes when martial arts expert Alex (Bob Poe), the fearless &quot;Shadow Warrior&quot;
	battles an army of blood-thirsty vampires to stop a huge illegal smuggling ring. Against
	overwhelming odds, Alex fights to destroy the smuggling operation before it's too late, 
	and in a final desperate showdown he must use all of his warrior's skill and cunning
	to survive against a legion of living dead!&quot;

-WHAT REALLY HAPPENS-
	Some vampires hop around, while another unrelated story about a gambler and hidden gold
	is introduced. Then some ninjas and a futuristic spaceman show up and kick some ass. An attempt
	to join the two plots occurs towards the end.

-Notes-
Two films edited into one, possibly also a third ('Ninja, the Violent Sorceror' (1986)). 
Hence the reason theres two stories, about vampires and gamblers, and also some 
ninjas thrown in the mix. Tomas Tang was 'infamous' (allthough he may be a psuedonym)
for taking multiple eastern movies and cutting them together and redubbing them. 

There are some shitty tracking problems at the beginning from the tape, but they
stop after the first 3 mintues and the movie is fine (ableit a bit of audio fading)
from then on.




